# [NVIDIA Studio Driver R595 (595.79) | Windows 11](https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/drivers/details/265478/)

NVIDIA Studio Drivers provide artists, creators, and 3D developers the best performance and reliability when working with creative applications. To achieve the highest level of reliability, Studio Drivers undergo extensive testing against multi-app creator workflows and multiple revisions of the top creative applications from Adobe to Autodesk and beyond.  

**Applications**   

The March NVIDIA Studio Driver provides optimal support for the latest new creative applications and updates including Topaz NeuroStream, Lightricks LTX-2.3, Windows ML support for VoiceMod, and the latest updates for FLUX.2 Klein 9B and ComfyUI.  

**Fixed Application Bugs**   

- Blackmagic Design: AV1 decode crash with multiple obu in one packet [5671098]
- The Ascent: Intermittent black bar on top of screen on GeForce RTX 50 Series GPUs [5859818]
- Total War: THREE KINGDOMS: Green artifacts appear on GeForce RTX 50 series [5745647]
- FINAL FANTASY XII The Zodiac Age crashes with fatal error after driver update [5741199]
- Call of Duty Modern Warfare (2019) displays image corruption after driver update [5733427]
- Quantum Break: Performance drops significantly on Act 4 Part 1 [5607678]
- Total War: Three Kingdoms: Artifacts may be observed during gameplay when Screen Space Reflections is enabled [5745647]
- Crimson Desert: Game crashes when launched on R595 drivers [5861012]
- Resident Evil Requiem: White glowing light/dots may appear in game when Subsurface Scattering is enabled [5915673]
- Star Citizen: Game client crashes when launched [5935027]

**Fixed General Bugs**   

- Color banding observed with SDR content when Windows Automatic Color Management enabled [5754551]
- Asus G14 may freeze on startup when Asus Ultimate Mode is enabled [5754849]
- When the graphics card is overclocked, GPU voltage may become capped, preventing it from boosting to expected levels [5934973]
- Intermittent application crash or driver timeout may be observed when playing multi-key DRM content in a browser on HDCP 1.x monitors [5934450]

---

## Overview

This package installs the latest Nvidia Studio Driver (aka the creator ready driver) for Windows 10/11 with the default settings. 
**This driver is meant for Nvidia GeForce GTX 1xxx series and GeForce RTX series (20xx and newer) cards, it also works with most Nvidia RTX / RTX PRO / Quadro cards.**
You can automate driver updates with `choco upgrade nvidia-studio-driver -y` in a scheduled task.
You can revert to previous driver versions with `choco install` and specifying the version. i.e. `choco install nvidia-studio-driver --version=581.29 -yf`

## Package Parameters

The following package parameters can be set to customize the installation.

  - `/SkipCompatCheck` - Skip the compatibility check that ensures your GPU is supported by this driver version. Use at your own risk.
  - `/RemoveOtherVersions` - If desired, remove other versions of the NVIDIA display driver from windows after install.
    - Can trigger an unexpected reboot (uncommon)
    - Removes any nvidia display driver that doesn't match the version of the newly installed version, only affects display driver other components are untouched.
    - Can help prevent windows from reverting to a 'newer' driver on reboot if reverting to an older version of the driver.

Example param usage with choco install command:
`choco install nvidia-studio-driver --params "'/RemoveOtherVersions'"`
